    "name": "S-VAE",
    "description": "The model described is an extension of the Variational Auto-Encoder (VAE). While standard VAEs use a Gaussian distribution for both the prior and posterior, failing when data has a latent hyperspherical structure, the authors propose using the von Mises-Fisher (vMF) distribution instead. This new architecture is called the Spherical VAE ($\\text{S-VAE}$), which results in a hyperspherical latent space. The $\\text{S-VAE}$ is claimed to be more suitable for capturing data with a hyperspherical latent structure and was shown to outperform a normal ($\\text{N-VAE}$) in low dimensions on other types of data.",
    "keywords": [
        "Variational Auto-Encoder",
        "VAE",
        "von Mises-Fisher",
        "vMF",
        "hyperspherical latent space",
        "S-VAE",
        "unsupervised machine learning"
    ],
